{
  "text": "(otherwise there is no such a calculus). This condition singles out a large class of quantum Minkowski spaces [CITATION_1] . From now on we assume that this condition is fulfilled. In particular, there exists a C-bimodule \u0393 \u22271 (of differential forms of the first order) and a linear mapping d : C \u2212\u2192 \u0393 \u22271 such that d(ab) = a(db) + (da)b, a, b \u2208 C, and dx i , i \u2208 S, form a basis of \u0393 \u22271 (as right C-module). We prove",
